<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL VIDEO RENTALS ; 'FIRM' KEEPS FIRM GRIP ON NO. 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is getting monotonous. Once again, "The Firm" holds off "Sleepless in 
Seattle" (No. 2) and "Dave" (No. 3). Though "Dave" seems doomed to permanent 
also-ran status, "Sleepless" may not be slumbering in second much longer. With 
Valentine's Day coming up, retailers are gearing up for a run on this romantic 
movie. If this doesn't boost it into the top spot, nothing will. Jean-Claude 
Van Damme's latest action movie, "Hard Target," may turn out to be his biggest 
rental hit. A $31.5-million grosser, it opened at No. 11 and could make the Top 
5. The silly "Coneheads" comedy, which debuted at No. 18, may get enough rental 
action from fans of low-brow comedy to push it into the Top 10. Expected to be 
huge box office, it registered just a mild $18.5-million gross. "Poetic 
Justice," starring Janet Jackson, started quietly, debuting at No. 34. It did 
decently in theaters--$27.5 million--and is expected to be a big hit among 
young black, music-oriented renters. 04,05,31,06,08 Rank Weeks Last on the Week 
Chart 1. "The Firm" 1 6 2. "Sleepless in Seattle" 2 7 3. "Dave" 3 6 4. "Rising 
Sun" 4 9 5. "True Romance" 7 4 6. "Robin Hood: Men in Tights" 12 3 7. "Hot 
Shots! Part Deux" 6 4 8. "Hocus Pocus" 9 4 9. "Cliffhanger" 5 11 10. "Guilty as 
Sin" 8 7 * "Last Action Hero" ... 1 * Many fans came to see this 
reality-juggling, Arnold Schwarzenegger movie but not nearly as many as 
expected. The gross--$50 million--was a drop in the bucket compared to what's 
needed for this staggeringly expensive movie to show a profit. Schwarzenegger 
couldn't lure moviegoers to this action-adventure movie, which got many bad 
reviews, but he should be able to attract renters. But the first week--a No. 13 
debut--wasn't great. Its position next week will be a better indication of its 
ultimate rental fate. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Billboard Publications Inc. DENNIS HUNT 
