<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEA VIEW LEAGUE WRESTLING; IRVINE SENDS NINE TO FINALS TO WIN EASILY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIK HAMILTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine dominated the Sea View League finals, sending nine of its 13 wrestlers 
into the finals with five winning titles Thursday at University High. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is really a relief from the pressure," Irvine Coach John Phillips 
said."Our guys wanted to have a good showing at this meet, and they certainly 
did that." 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine finished with 208.5 points. University was second with 124, followed by 
Woodbridge (96), Tustin (85), Saddleback (67), Newport Harbor (60), Santa 
Margarita (53) and Corona del Mar (42). 
</P>
<P>
 Going into the finals, sixth-ranked Irvine (13-2-1, 6-0-1) was tied with 
University (12-13-1, 6-0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 "When we tied Uni back in January, that was our wake-up call," Phillips said. 
"Since then, we have won two tournaments and took second in another. We wanted 
to show some people that we didn't roll over and die." 
</P>
<P>
 For Irvine, Peter Hamilton (103), Justin Meier (125), Chris Testerman (130), 
Lambert Lo (140) and Doug Reid (152) won their championship matches and will 
advance to the Southern Section individual championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Other winners were: University's Koh Yamada (112), Woodbridge's Tim Lee (119), 
Santa Margarita's Andy Vander Ahe (135), University's James Stephenson (145), 
Newport Harbor's Chris Edwards (160), Tustin's Shawn Ghotbi (171), Woodbridge 
Jessie Liu (189) and Saddleback heavyweight Jim Ambriz. ERIK HAMILTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
