<HEADLINE>
<P>
MASTER'S EARNS 12TH CONSECUTIVE WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Master's College men's basketball team made visiting California Chrisitian 
look out of its league with a 106-48 nonconference victory Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mustangs shot 68% from the floor and outrebounded California Christian, 
50-12.The victory was the 12th in a row for Master's, which improved to 23-3 in 
the NAIA with four games remaining on the schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 Leo Gorauskas, a 6-foot-9 freshman center from Sao Paulo, Brazil, finished 
with a game-high 27 points and 14 rebounds for the Mustangs. He also had two 
assists, two blocked shots and two steals. Guard James Mosley made three of 
four three-point attempts en route to scoring 19. Three other Master's players 
scored in double figures. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mustangs shot 68% in each half and scored 63 points in each half. 
California Christian scored 24 points in each half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
