<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / BIG WEST ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 97, Nevada 72 -- It began as a rout for Nevada (9-11, 5-7) 
but wound up being a rout for the Titans. 
</P>
<P>
 They trailed by 17 points with 11 minutes left in the first half, then stormed 
back for a rout of the Wolf Pack before 873 in Titan Gym. 
</P>
<P>
 Five Fullerton players, led by Darren Little's career-high 24 points, scored 
in double figures, as the Titans (5-15, 3-9) beat an NCAA team at home for the 
first time this season. MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
