<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; VALENCIA'S GRAND SLAM LEADS ORANGE COAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nick Valencia hit a fourth-inning grand slam to help Orange Coast to an 11-1 
victory over Southwestern in the opening round of the Southwestern tournament 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast (3-1) dedicated the game to the memory of Michael Copp, the 
college's sports academic adviser who died Feb. 3 of a heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Sunderman, Scott MacDermott, Chris Yakura and Valencia each had two hits 
for OCC. Yakura was two for two and is six for six in his last two games. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Southwestern tournament game: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 10, Grossmont 4 -- Host Rancho Santiago, the defending State 
champion, scored five runs in the third inning to take a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Bellovich and Daryle Ward had doubles for Rancho Santiago (3-1), which 
started the season as the top-ranked team in the nation by Baseball America. 
</P>
<P>
 Ethan Wyckoff (1-0) pitched the first six innings for the victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
