<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / WCC ROUNDUP; MAZURIE LEADS LOYOLA RALLY, PORTLAND FALLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bill Mazurie came off the bench and scored all of his 18 points during a 
second-half rally as Loyola Marymount defeated Portland, 88-79, Thursday night 
in a West Coast Conference game at Portland to extend its winning streak to 
three games. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lions, 5-15 and 4-5 in the WCC, have won four of their last five. 
</P>
<P>
 Two baskets by Matt Houle gave the Pilots (11-13, 4-5) a 61-49 lead with 10:45 
left, but the Lions went on a 17-4 run in the next five minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzaga 66, Pepperdine 56 -- The first-place Bulldogs won their 25th 
consecutive game at the Martin Centre in Spokane. 
</P>
<P>
 It marked the first time Gonzaga (16-5, 8-1) has swept the season series from 
the Waves (12-9, 4-5) since the joining the conference in 1979. The Bulldogs 
won, 70-48, last week at Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
 Pepperdine, which trailed, 43-31, with 14:32 left, tied the score at 50-50 on 
LeRoi O'Brien's basket with 7:18 left. But the Waves were outscored, 16-6, the 
rest of the game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
