<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: TRISTAR PRESIDENT EXPECTED TO HEAD COMBINED UNIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jon Feltheimer, president of TriStar Television, is expected to be named head 
of a combined TriStar Television and Columbia Pictures Television at Sony 
Studios. 
</P>
<P>
 Sony declined to comment, but TV executives were buzzing all week about the 
changes afoot at Sony's network TV production division. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the rumors, Feltheimer will oversee both divisions, leaving open 
the fate of Scott Siegler, president of Columbia Pictures TV. TriStar TV under 
Feltheimer has been on a hot streak with shows such as "Mad about You" on NBC 
and "The Nanny" on CBS. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nancy Kirkpatrick has been named vice president of publicity at Warner Bros. 
</P>
<P>
 * Castle Rock Entertainment has promoted Gregory M. Paul to executive vice 
president and general counsel. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jeffrey Schlesinger has been named president of Warner Bros. International 
Television Distribution. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ed Trainor is the new senior vice president of information systems for 
Paramount Pictures. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ron Kramer is the new national director of member, chapter and branch 
services for the National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences. 
</P>
<P>
 * Debra Stein is the new vice president of public relations at Live 
Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 * Network 1 has named Diane L. Karrmann to director of programming and 
scheduling. 
</P>
<P>
 * Fashion photographer Douglas Strock has been named director of marketing and 
photography for Star Hollywood Headshots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
