COLLEGE ROUNDUP; AZUSA PACIFIC BEATS CAL LUTHERAN, 9-8 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Despite three hits each by David Chapman and Joe Gordon, Cal Lutheran dropped 
its season opener to Azusa Pacific, 9-8, Thursday in a nonconference game 
called after eight innings because of darkness at Azusa. 
</P>
<P>
 Gordon had two doubles and drove in two runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Kings River 3, Glendale 2 -- The Vaqueros squandered a two-run, ninth-inning 
lead and lost in the 10th inning at the Kings River tournament in Reedley. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale's John Nall had a one-hitter through eight innings but allowed a 
single and a triple in the ninth. Reliever Bryan Warner hit a batter with the 
bases loaded and two out to force in the tying run. 
</P>
<P>
 Kings River (2-1) scored in the 10th after a Glendale error. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 13, Cerro Coso 7 -- Eric Cole went five for five, including a 
home run and two triples, and drove in four runs for the Marauders (1-1) in a 
nonleague game at Cerro Coso. 
</P>
<P>
 Rickey Dominguez (1-0) limited Cerro Coso to seven hits and three earned runs 
in seven innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 6, Mt. San Jacinto 6 -- The Raiders (1-0-1) outhit Mt. San Jacinto, 
11-5, but the game ended a tie because of darkness. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark owned a 5-2 lead after seven innings, but Mt. San Jacinto rallied to 
tie it, 6-6, by scoring twice with two out in the ninth. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission 14, Cuesta 4 -- Erik Lazarus drove in three runs with a home run and a 
triple to lead Mission (3-0) to a first-round victory in the Chaffey 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Ray Rivera (2-0) threw a complete game for the Free Spirit. 
