<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
CONTRACT AWARDED FOR REBUILDING SIMI FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Caltrans officials awarded a $9.7-million contract to a Fontana construction 
company Thursday to rebuild the eastbound quake-damaged portions of the Simi 
Valley Freeway in the north San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Brutoco Engineering and Construction is expected to reconstruct the underpass 
and the Bull Creek Canyon bridge on the freeway within 100 days.To meet the 
deadline, Caltrans officials say, crews will work 24 hours a day, seven days a 
week. 
</P>
<P>
 A bonus of $50,000 a day will be given to the construction company for work 
finished ahead of the deadline. If the deadline is not met, the contractor will 
be penalized $50,000 for each late day. 
</P>
<P>
 "Because of the urgent need to put Los Angeles and its transportation system 
back on its feet, we expect to have this key project completed within 100 
days," Caltrans Director James W. van Loben Sels said. 
</P>
<P>
 The westbound lanes of the freeway will opened first, using the existing 
structure, which is being shored up. Once repaired, this will hold three lanes 
of traffic in each direction -- two mixed-flow lanes and one car-pool lane. 
</P>
