<HEADLINE>
<P>
VAN, INMATE BUS COLLIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department bus carrying jail inmates collided 
Thursday with a van, causing minor injuries to 40 prisoners and to five 
passengers in the other vehicle, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Wells, a Los Angeles Fire Department spokesman, said the accident occurred 
about 6:30 p.m. near Florence and Dalton avenues. Wells said the cause was 
unclear and under investigation. 
</P>
<P>
 Wells said the van passengers were taken to Martin Luther King Jr./Drew 
Medical Center and to St. Francis Medical Center. The inmates, who mostly 
complained of neck and back pain, were taken to the Men's Central Jail, which 
was deemed a more secure location for treatment of their injuries, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
