<P>
 A tornado touched down Thursday in the southern part of this Central Valley 
city, damaging about a dozen homes, Butte County officials said.No injuries 
were reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The twister was spotted about 2:30 p.m. near Las Plumas High School. 
</P>
<P>
 About five homes sustained serious damage, including one that lost its roof. 
The tornado also broke windows, damaged fences and caused a short power outage 
to about 250 homes, said Fred Svetz, Butte County emergency services director. 
</P>
