<P>
 Workers' Comp Insurer Sued: Three employers have filed a class-action suit 
claiming that California's biggest workers' compensation carrier, State 
Compensation Insurance Fund, has intentionally or negligently allowed its 
customers to be improperly overcharged for their coverage.The suit, filed in 
Orange County Superior Court, alleges that the insurer overstated by $500 
million the insurance reserves it has held over the last two years to cover 
potential claims against its customers. The suit says that the misreporting, in 
turn, enabled the insurer to inflate premiums for employers. The insurer, also 
known as SCIF, denied the accusation and said the plaintiffs should have 
submitted their complaint to state regulators to try to resolve the dispute 
before filing a lawsuit. 
