<HEADLINE>
<P>
VIACOM SAYS QVC IS CHEATING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Viacom Inc. on Thursday charged that QVC Network Inc., its rival in the 
bidding war for Paramount Communications Inc., is cheating by attempting to 
improve its offer before the contest's Monday deadline, and it called on 
Paramount to take "vigorous action." 
</P>
<P>
 Viacom noted that QVC has hinted in recent meetings with securities analysts 
and traders that it might provide guarantees for the price of the stock portion 
of its Paramount bid.Those guarantees would come from having one of QVC's 
investors, BellSouth Corp., agree to purchase QVC stock in the future, 
according to published reports. Viacom denounced QVC's efforts as "a backdoor 
attempt by QVC to change its offer after the bidders' Feb. 1 deadline." Viacom 
said that, in response, it will consider "all options and remedies." Paramount 
had no immediate comment. QVC denied the accusations. 
</P>
