<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: ACME HOLDINGS TO TAKE FOURTH-QUARTER CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Acme Holdings Inc. of Irvine said it expects to take a charge of $2 million 
for the fourth quarter to cover reorganization costs, including future lease 
commitments and severance and relocation costs. 
</P>
<P>
 In a press release, the company said it also expects to report a 
fourth-quarter charge of about $3.5 million for the write-down of underutilized 
assets, adjustments to inventory, additional reserves for uninsured liability 
claims and bad debts. 
</P>
<P>
 Acme said it expects its quarterly results -- before reorganization and other 
charges -- to be "below third-quarter 1993 levels." 
</P>
<P>
 The company reported losses of about $2.2 million for the third quarter and 
$5.13 million for the nine months ended Sept. 30. The nine months included a 
charge of $649,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Acme estimates that total revenue for the fourth quarter and the year ended 
Dec. 31 will be about $16.6 million and $63.5 million, respectively, compared 
to $17.7 million and $68.6 million a year earlier. The company said that 
audited fourth-quarter and year-end results will be released around March 1. 
</P>
