<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; 2 ROBBERS SOUGHT IN BEATING, STABBING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard police are looking for two suspects who beat and stabbed a man in front 
of the Lucky's Supermarket on West Hemlock Street in Oxnard, an Oxnard Police 
Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 John Donovan, 48, of Santa Paula was taken Tuesday night to St. John's 
Regional Medical Center, where he was treated for a stab wound and lacerations, 
a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Donovan was walking to his car parked near the supermarket when he was struck 
on the back of the head by one of the men, the police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that while Donovan lay semiconscious on the ground, he 
attempted to ward off the attack and was stabbed in the neck by another man. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects then rifled through Donovan's pockets, stealing his car keys, 
credit cards and $75 in cash, before fleeing on foot, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 No arrests have been made and the robbery is under investigation, the 
spokesman said. SCOTT HADLY 
