CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Municipal Court judge on Thursday ordered a 44-year-old man to stand trial 
on charges that he abducted his former girlfriend outside her Thousand Oaks 
church, handcuffed her and held her at gunpoint for about 90 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County Judge Bruce A. Clark ordered Thomas Robles of Norwalk to appear 
Feb. 18 for an arraignment in Superior Court. 
</P>
<P>
 He is charged with one count of kidnaping and a special allegation that he 
used a firearm during the crime. 
</P>
<P>
 During a preliminary hearing Thursday, Keely Okada testified that Robles 
forced her into his car as she left church near Sandberg Street and Keats 
Avenue on Dec. 17. She said he put a hand over her mouth because she was 
screaming. 
</P>
<P>
 Once in Robles' car, the woman said, she was handcuffed to the front seat as 
he drove around Thousand Oaks and Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
 She said she had broken off a relationship with Robles this past September, 
when they stopped living together after about six months. DWAYNE BRAY 
