<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOT PROPS / THE WORD ON WHAT'S HIP AND WHAT'S HYPE: THAT'S RIGHT, FOLKS! 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROSE APODACA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Candy and flowers are sweet but so, uh, traditional. Try an unexpected source 
like the Warner Bros. Studio stores in South Coast Plaza, Costa Mesa, and, as 
of today's grand opening, in the Brea Mall. "There are gifts that are 
sentimental, with a sense of humor for all ages," notes spokeswoman Liz 
Gardner. And many have a romantic slant: Check out silver-plated pins ($10) or 
a box containing a "fat-free" T-shirt ($20), both featuring Looney Tunes 
couples. More Than Friends 
</P>
<P>
 Leave it to Tiffany & Co. to remember that one of the most significant aspects 
of a relationship between two people is being friends. Hence the legendary 
jeweler's recent Friendship Collection of bangles and rings in white, yellow or 
pink gold adorned by a tiny heart of diamond, amethyst or tourmaline ($375 to 
$2,600). "It connotes all kinds of things -- messages of endearment, courtship 
or a promise of something more," says spokeswoman Jo Ellen Qualls. She adds 
that the line has been well-received by the company's younger clients. Love on 
the Inside 
</P>
<P>
 Undergarments are among the most popular gifts at Valentine's Day -- but don't 
assume it's sexy lingerie. Joe Boxer, famous for its novelty print boxer shorts 
and pajamas, counts this time as one of its busiest of the year. "If you're 
going to say it," says spokeswoman Denise Slattery, "we suggest saying it with 
underwear." Skivvies covered with red hearts or ruby lips ($14) have become a 
classic for the San Francisco-based label. Gals who don't care to wear his 
things can turn to the Joe Boxer Girlfriend! line for Cupid jammies ($34) or 
the "love me, love me not" sleep T-shirt ($18). Personal Touches 
</P>
<P>
 Chocolate mint. Raspberry. Vanilla. These scrumptious flavors don't come in a 
box for your honey but, rather, in a collector glass bottle ($12.50) that the 
two of you can indulge in with a mutual rubdown. Moonrose in San Juan 
Capistrano carries a full range of Kama Sutra oils that owner Sue Toler says 
are "popular for sensual massages." There are also weekender kits filled with 
samples of flavored oils, cornstarch powders, creams and soaps for $18; the big 
gift drum is $60. The store also sells the Aura Casia line of essential oils 
that can be specially blended with massage oil to fit personal tastes for under 
$20. ROSE APODACA 
</P>
</TEXT>
